%% The load-bearing cross-node contract: window.__GAME__
%% W1 drafts assertions over it → W2 finalizes + exposes the accessor →
%% W4 populates it from REAL state → W5 reads it to assert. The oracle is immutable.
sequenceDiagram
  autonumber
  participant W1 as W1 · Spec (Designer)
  participant W2 as W2 · Scaffold (Coder)
  participant H as window.__GAME__ hook
  participant W4 as W4 · Implement (Coder)
  participant W5 as W5 · Verify (Playtester)

  Note over W1,W5: The filesystem is the contract — nodes hand off ONLY via on-disk artifacts

  W1->>H: DRAFT assertions over the hook (observe player.y / score / status …)
  Note right of W1: writes spec/gdd.json — the IMMUTABLE oracle

  W2->>H: FINALIZE canonical accessor (superset of W1 draft) and template EXPOSES it
  Note right of W2: template-contract.md §3: ready/status/scene/player/score/entities + snapshot()

  W4->>H: POPULATE from REAL state (score via registry · status set at the real win/lose point)
  Note right of W4: anti-reward-hack — implement the mechanic so the observable is genuinely true

  W5->>H: READ to assert (setup → input → observe vs expect)
  H-->>W5: live values

  alt every assertion passes
    W5->>W5: emit VALIDATION_PASSED
  else any assertion fails
    W5->>W4: bounded ≤3 self-fix — edit src/** GAME CODE only
    Note over W4,W5: NEVER edit gdd / assertions / hook / harness — the oracle stays immutable
  end
